title: 4.4.4.2.2 - Cryo-hydrologic warming
section 4_4_4_2_2

  |Percolation and refreezing of surface meltwater that drains through the ice column may alter the thermal regime of the {Glossary.*Ice_sheet ice sheet} on decadal time scale. This process is known as cryo-hydrologic warming, and it could affect ice flow.


  

